{
  "page": "Rohanne Tarbeck",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The canonicity of the character presented in this article is currently unclear. They are not mentioned in the published works of <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a>. However, they are mentioned in an expanded version of the Westerlands chapter from <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_and_Fire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The World of Ice and Fire\">The World of Ice and Fire</a></i> that was published on Martin's website a few months before the book release date.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Until further information comes out, they should be considered a semi-canon character.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarbeck\" title=\"House Tarbeck\"><img alt=\"House Tarbeck.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/85/House_Tarbeck.svg/50px-House_Tarbeck.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/85/House_Tarbeck.svg/75px-House_Tarbeck.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/8/85/House_Tarbeck.svg/100px-House_Tarbeck.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\">Rohanne Tarbeck</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/Silent_sisters\" title=\"Silent sisters\"><img alt=\"Star of the Faith.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/50px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/75px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/91/Star_of_the_Faith.svg/100px-Star_of_the_Faith.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Three_Rohannes_by_coldraindropsss.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Three Rohannes by coldraindropsss.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/48/Three_Rohannes_by_coldraindropsss.jpg/300px-Three_Rohannes_by_coldraindropsss.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"296\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/4/48/Three_Rohannes_by_coldraindropsss.jpg/450px-Three_Rohannes_by_coldraindropsss.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/4/48/Three_Rohannes_by_coldraindropsss.jpg/600px-Three_Rohannes_by_coldraindropsss.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Rohanne Tarbeck (right) with <a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_of_Tyrosh\" title=\"Rohanne of Tyrosh\">Rohanne of Tyrosh</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_Webber\" title=\"Rohanne Webber\">Rohanne Webber</a> by coldraindropsss</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiances</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarbeck\" title=\"House Tarbeck\">House Tarbeck</a></li><li><a href=\"/index.php/Silent_sisters\" title=\"Silent sisters\">Silent sisters</a></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_240_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">240&#160;AC</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan Tarbeck</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Mother</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn Reyne</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Issue</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Last_Lord_Tarbeck\" title=\"Last Lord Tarbeck\">last Lord Tarbeck</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Rohanne Tarbeck</b> was a member of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Tarbeck\" title=\"House Tarbeck\">House Tarbeck</a> and the elder daughter of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Tarbeck\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ellyn Tarbeck\">Ellyn Tarbeck</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rohanne_Tarbeck&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>According to a semi-canon source,<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn Tarbeck</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Named_after\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Named after\">named</a> her after <a href=\"/index.php/Rohanne_Webber\" title=\"Rohanne Webber\">Rohanne Webber</a>, an attack against the widowed <a href=\"/index.php/Gerold_Lannister\" title=\"Gerold Lannister\">Gerold Lannister</a>, Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>, as his wife Rohanne had disappeared mysteriously. \n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Reyne-Tarbeck_rebellion\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Reyne-Tarbeck rebellion\">Reyne-Tarbeck rebellion</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a> ordered the executions of Rohanne's unnamed husband and her father, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan Tarbeck</a>. Rohanne and her sister <a href=\"/index.php/Cyrelle_Tarbeck\" title=\"Cyrelle Tarbeck\">Cyrelle</a> were taken captive during Tywin's assault on <a href=\"/index.php/Tarbeck_Hall\" title=\"Tarbeck Hall\">Tarbeck Hall</a>. Some stories claim that Tywin ordered their <a href=\"/index.php/Tongue_mutilation\" title=\"Tongue mutilation\">tongues removed</a> before they were forced to join the <a href=\"/index.php/Silent_sisters\" title=\"Silent sisters\">silent sisters</a>. Rohanne's three-year-old son, the <a href=\"/index.php/Last_Lord_Tarbeck\" title=\"Last Lord Tarbeck\">last Lord Tarbeck</a>, disappeared during the assault.<sup id=\"cite_ref-sample_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-sample-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Rohanne_Tarbeck&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Unknown<br />two wives</td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Walderan_Tarbeck\" title=\"Walderan Tarbeck\">Walderan</a><br /><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;Note 1&#93;</a></sup></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Ellyn_Reyne\" title=\"Ellyn Reyne\">Ellyn<br />Reyne</a></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr><tr align=\"center\"><td style=\"border-right:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td style=\"border-right:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr>\n<tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em; height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em; height:1em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black;\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td style=\"border-r